International Brief -- L'Oreal S.A.:
   French Firm Says Revenue
   Increased 10.2% During 1991
The group said its cosmetics division had reported an
increase of 11.7% in sales last year, while sales of its
Synthelabo pharmaceutical subsidiary rose by 3.8%. L'Oreal
didn't provide absolute numbers in its breakdown.
   On a strictly comparable basis, using identical exchange
rates and structures, L'Oreal said its consolidated revenue
grew by only 9.5% in 1991. Sales of cosmetics rose 10.4%
while those of the Synthelabo pharmaceutical division were up
8.2%, on the same basis.